Another process that we consider is the liberation of photoelectrons in the X123 Be window that can eventually be detected and appear in the spectrum. These events will occur at energies lower than the initial photon distribution that created the photoelectrons through the energy loss processes in migrating to the window surface, the negative bias of the X123 detector front surface and transport through the detector dead layer. The resulting contribution would be a continuum distribution at low energies (Eph≤1.5keV\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
