				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}${\approx}\,2.1$\end{document} times photospheric), and one of the latest photosphere (Caffau et al., 2011) abundances. The MinXSS instrument temperature response begins to deviate for plasma temperatures greater than 2 MK, primarily because of the ions of the low-FIP elements. Figure 7
