				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$y = a(x^{b})$\end{document}, between the MinXSS-1/X123 total counts and the total radiative energy greater than 1 keV, which is not quite linear. The data in the scatter plots (Figure 10B – D) are from 10 June – 30 November 2016. The coefficient of 2.2×10−8Jcounts−1m−2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
